content: If we are connected with a parent/spouse and the voter isn't there, what is the protocol? Should I mark it down as a wrong number? I've had this a few times, but specifically today, the number was for the voter's father, and he said she was away at college. She voted yesterday, but he doesn't know for who.
If the phone number is correct, but the wrong person answered use busy/call back. If the phone number no longer belongs to the person you can use wring number
"Call Back" since that seems like the only way to get the right person on a shared phone line.
